# Cursor Rules for POS Pipeline Core ETL

## Python Environment Configuration

This project uses an Anaconda environment. Configure the Python interpreter based on your operating system:

### Windows
The Python interpreter should be located at:
- `C:\Users\mzenk\anaconda3\envs\pos-etl\python.exe` (if using Anaconda)
- `C:\Users\<username>\miniconda3\envs\pos-etl\python.exe` (if using Miniconda)

### macOS
The Python interpreter should be located at:
- `~/anaconda3/envs/pos-etl/bin/python` (if using Anaconda)
- `~/miniconda3/envs/pos-etl/bin/python` (if using Miniconda)

## Environment Setup

If the environment doesn't exist, create it with:
```bash
# Windows (PowerShell)
conda create -n pos-etl python=3.10
conda activate pos-etl
pip install -e .[dev]

# macOS (Terminal)
conda create -n pos-etl python=3.10
conda activate pos-etl
pip install -e .[dev]
```

